<subSubSection pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1437,931,1390]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1040,1066]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Ecology</emphasis>
. Largely intertidal; within or on the fringe of red mangrove swamps, apparently able to tolerate very low salinities (
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G." box="[314,540,1075,1102]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="559 - 573" refId="ref72254" refString="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G. (1974) Three new species of porcellanid crabs (Crustacea, Decapoda, Porcellanidae) from the Bay of Panama and adjacent Caribbean waters. Bulletin of Marine Science, 23 (3), 559 - 573." type="journal article" year="1974">Gore &amp; Abele 1974</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1437,931,1390]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1112,1138]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gore &amp; Abele" authorityYear="1974" box="[325,537,1111,1137]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindae">
<emphasis box="[325,537,1111,1137]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Petrolisthes lindae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is largely sympatric with the closely related 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Gibbes" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[1058,1180,1112,1137]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">
<emphasis box="[1058,1180,1112,1137]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. armatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Haig, 1960" authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1960" box="[1197,1436,1111,1137]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilii">
<emphasis box="[1197,1300,1111,1137]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. nobilii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[1309,1436,1111,1137]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Glassell, 1945" authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1945" box="[336,633,1147,1174]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robsonae">
<emphasis box="[336,466,1147,1173]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. robsonae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Glassell, S. A." box="[473,633,1147,1174]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="223 - 229" refId="ref71988" refString="Glassell, S. A. (1945) Four new species of North American crabs of the genus Petrolisthes. Proceedings of the Washington Academy of Sciences, 35, 223 - 229." type="journal article" year="1945">Glassell, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see below). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gore &amp; Abele" authorityYear="1974" box="[900,997,1147,1173]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindae">
<emphasis box="[900,997,1147,1173]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lindae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has just one tooth and a lobe on the P1 carpus (
<emphasis box="[240,271,1184,1209]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">vs.</emphasis>
two or three teeth, as in the other species); the epibranchial tooth is either vestigial or absent (
<emphasis box="[1317,1347,1184,1209]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">vs.</emphasis>
distinct in the other species); and the granulation of the carapace slightly from each of the other three species (
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G." pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="559 - 573" refId="ref72254" refString="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G. (1974) Three new species of porcellanid crabs (Crustacea, Decapoda, Porcellanidae) from the Bay of Panama and adjacent Caribbean waters. Bulletin of Marine Science, 23 (3), 559 - 573." type="journal article" year="1974">Gore &amp; Abele 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G." box="[223,283,1255,1282]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref72307" refString="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G. (1976) Shallow water porcelain crabs from the Pacific coast of Panama and adjacent Caribbean waters (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 237, 1 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.237" type="journal article" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
). The closeness of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gore &amp; Abele" authorityYear="1974" box="[500,599,1255,1281]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindae">
<emphasis box="[500,599,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lindae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to these three species led 
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G." box="[900,1136,1255,1282]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="559 - 573" refId="ref72254" refString="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G. (1974) Three new species of porcellanid crabs (Crustacea, Decapoda, Porcellanidae) from the Bay of Panama and adjacent Caribbean waters. Bulletin of Marine Science, 23 (3), 559 - 573." type="journal article" year="1974">Gore &amp; Abele (1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G." box="[1148,1205,1255,1282]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref72307" refString="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G. (1976) Shallow water porcelain crabs from the Pacific coast of Panama and adjacent Caribbean waters (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 237, 1 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.237" type="journal article" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
) question whether a hybridisation between two of the above species may have occurred in the past, resulting in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gore &amp; Abele" authorityYear="1974" box="[1189,1288,1291,1317]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindae">
<emphasis box="[1189,1288,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lindae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Adults of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gore &amp; Abele" authorityYear="1974" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lindae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1945" box="[275,405,1327,1353]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robsonae">
<emphasis box="[275,405,1327,1353]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. robsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as juveniles of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gore &amp; Abele" authorityYear="1974" box="[672,769,1327,1353]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindae">
<emphasis box="[672,769,1327,1353]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lindae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Gibbes" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[782,902,1328,1353]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">
<emphasis box="[782,902,1328,1353]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. armatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1945" box="[955,1085,1327,1353]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robsonae">
<emphasis box="[955,1085,1327,1353]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. robsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are particularly difficult to tell apart (
<bibRefCitation author="Abele, L. G. &amp; Kim, W." box="[222,443,1363,1390]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref69810" refString="Abele, L. G. &amp; Kim, W. (1989) The decapod crustaceans of the Panama Canal. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 482, 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.482" type="journal article" year="1989">Abele &amp; Kim 1989</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
